<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-395-384  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 395 384.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 23 1990 v4 n16 p16(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OMB seeks input on FILS expansion. (Office of Management andBudget)(Federal Information Inventory and Locator System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kellner, Mark A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Office of Management and Budget has called for public commentregarding whether to alter its Federal Information Inventory andLocator System (FILS).andP;  Comments are due to OMB by May 21, 1990and will be integrated into a study of FILS undertaken by a teamof Syracuse University researchers.andP;  Current content of FILS is oflimited value to the public; it includes data on the names andnumbers of forms that government agencies produce and distributebut omits information on what kind of data the forms are designedto collect.andP;  Librarians and non-profit groups have expressedsupport for an expanded FILS re-designed to facilitate publicaccess to government information.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Statute:   Paperwork Reduction Act of 1980 (interpretation and construction).andO;Topic:     United States. Office of Management and BudgetData Base DesignInformation Storage and RetrievalSyracuse UniversityForms ManagementFederal Information Inventory and Locator System (Data base).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>